bilingual.source: The ice sculpture was shaped into a swan.
bilingual.target: 冰雕被成形成一只天鹅。

bilingual.source: The cookie dough was shaped into stars and hearts.
bilingual.target: 饼干面团被成形成星星和心形。

bilingual.source: The artist shaped the clay into a beautiful vase.
bilingual.target: 艺术家把黏土成形成一个漂亮的花瓶。

bilingual.source: Language eis shaped by, and shapes, human thought.
bilingual.target: 人的思想形成了语言，而语言又形成了人的思想。 。

bilingual.source: This shaped people's perceptions of each other.
bilingual.target: 这使人们形成了对彼此的看法。

bilingual.source: But mountains are shaped by forces other than uplift.
bilingual.target: 但使山峰形态的形成的外力不止隆升。

bilingual.source: It has been shaped by the Pleistocene Glaciation.
bilingual.target: 东海岸是在更新世的冰川作用下形成的。

bilingual.source: Seed funicle inflated at base, appendage stomach-shaped.
bilingual.target: 种子珠柄膨大的在基部，附属物胃形成。

bilingual.source: Your life is formed, shaped and created from your thoughts.
bilingual.target: 你的思维形成、塑造和创造你的生活。

bilingual.source: Language is shaped by, and shapes, human thought.
bilingual.target: 人的思想形成了语言，而语言又影响了人的思考。

yingyinNormal.en: Did you do a picture of Emma? Yes. On a cake shaped like a bunny.
yingyinNormal.zh: 那你一定放爱玛的照片喽？当然，在一个兔子形的蛋糕。

yingyinNormal.en: Everyone will see my oddly shaped uvula. You don't want that, do you?
yingyinNormal.zh: 大家都会看着我形态奇异的小舌头。你也不想看到这个画面吧？

yingyinNormal.en: Oh, I can't, honey. I'm gonna go get my eyebrows shaped. I am not happy.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我没空，我要去修眉，这样的眉毛像哭丧着脸。

yingyinNormal.en: Well, it just so happens that I do have a dinosaur shaped ice-lolly! Dine-Saw! Grrrr!
yingyinNormal.zh: 好吧，恰巧我确实有一个恐龙状的冰棒！恐龙！哦！

yingyinNormal.en: That is not brightly colored or shaped like a dinosaur. Hold on, guys. It's broccoli! Yucky!
yingyinNormal.zh: 这个颜色不鲜亮，并且形状像个恐龙，等等，伙计们，是西兰花！讨厌！

yingyinNormal.en: Or it could be shaped like a saddle. We call this negatively curved or open. Or it could be flat.
yingyinNormal.zh: 或者它也可能呈马鞍形。我们称之为负弯曲或负开放。又或者它也可能是扁平状。

yingyinNormal.en: Oh, David, get one for us too. Oh, and see if they have a heart shaped one. And with mirrors on the ceiling.
yingyinNormal.zh: 大卫，也帮我们确定一下，还有看看他们有没有心型的床，而且天花板上要有镜子。

yingyinNormal.en: The chicken nuggets you were sure were human nuggets. The strangely shaped cloud that was following you around town.
yingyinNormal.zh: 还有你坚信是人肉做的鸡块，还有那朵奇形怪状的在城里老跟踪你的云。

yingyinNormal.en: Okay, this is a typical lightning-bearer thing. Right there, it's like, 'Hello, who wants one of my phallic-shaped man-cakes?'
yingyinNormal.zh: 这就是典型的闪电使者行为。就像是“嗨，谁要来一根我的阴茎形状的蛋糕？”

yingyinNormal.en: Windows that don't open, multi user linens, keys shaped like credit cards as if one walks around with unassigned slots in one's wallet.
yingyinNormal.zh: 打不开的窗户，N个人用过的床单，卡式的钥匙，好像谁的钱包都有空的卡槽似的。

yingyinNormal.en: Well, it just so happens that I do have a dinosaur shaped ice-lolly. Dine-Saw. George, you should eat your ice-lolly before it melts. Dine-Saw.
yingyinNormal.zh: 是吗，那真是太巧了，我这里正好有卖恐龙形状的雪糕恐龙。乔治，快帮雪糕吃完，不然要化了。恐龙。

yingyinNormal.en: Nearly finished, that's the lid. There's just this funny shaped bit left. Where does that go? That's the teapot handle, Miss. Rabbit. Oh, so it is.
yingyinNormal.zh: 基本上完成了，这是盖子。这个还剩一块很搞笑的。这块要粘在哪里？这是茶壶的手柄，兔小姐。哦，是的。

yingyinNormal.en: Nearly finished, that's the lid. There's just this funny shaped bit left. Where does that go? That's the teapot's handle, Miss. Rabbit. Oh, so it is.
yingyinNormal.zh: 基本上完成了，这是盖子。这个还剩一块很搞笑的。这块要粘在哪里？这是茶壶的手柄，兔小姐。哦，确实是的。

yingyinNormal.en: Ever since the Colonists arrived in 1624, New York has been continuously shaped by the waves of immigrants drawn here by the promise of hope, and liberty.
yingyinNormal.zh: 自从 1624 年殖民地居民来到此地，纽约一直塑造了移民浪潮，因为这个地方代表了希望和自由的承诺。

yingyinNormal.en: This epic journey from the air will discover how ancient traditions engineering, agriculture and natural wonders shaped this great nation and continue to forge modern-day China.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这次诗般美妙的空中之旅会向我们诉说古老传统、工业、农业和自然奇景是如何让描绘了当今中国的可爱面容。

yingyinNormal.en: 400 miles away, deep in the heart to the Hunan Province is another epic holy site, but this time formed without human hands. A natural formation shaped by the area's unusual geology, Tian Men Shan, known as the heavens gate cave.
yingyinNormal.zh: 六百四十公里开外，在湖南省的腹地，坐落着另一个史诗级圣地，但是这回却并非出自人类手笔，而是大自然的鬼斧神工。天门山，也即通往天堂的大门。

direction_info.description:
数据源自2015-2022年8年间全国卷和自主命题省市高考卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2015-2022年全国卷高考试卷，包括阅读、完形、单选、填空、听力、改错、写作等所有题型。

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>
精选各省市考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2015-2022年8年间全国卷和自主命题省市高考卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。
